title: BGC1: All Fights & Drama In Order [Part 3] (HD)
description:
00:00 - Aimee vs. Zara
02:05 - Aimee vs. DeAnn & Kerry
02:58 - DeAnn vs. Zara
03:23 - Jodie vs. DeAnn
06:11 - Jodie, Kerry, Aimee & DeAnn vs. Strangers & Zara

The original season of The Bad Girls Club (BGC) is perhaps the most overlooked season of all time but that doesn't mean they shouldn't get the recognition they deserve. After all, they did revolutionise the franchise into 16 following seasons. The original castmates were Zara, Leslie, Ripsi, Kerry, Aimee, Jodie & Ty. Ripsi was the first to be kicked off the show and was replaced by DeAnn. Ty was the second to be kicked off and Leslie quit not long after which resulted in them being replaced by Joanna and Andrea. The drama wasn't as extreme as later seasons as the purpose was to actually change into a grown, mature woman.

No copyright intended.

title: Bad Girls Club: The Greatest Social Experiment That Never Was
description:
Subscribe to Naomi Cannibal: https://bit.ly/3f74yW3 | Enable ALL notifs!

Across 17 season, Bad Girls Club has blessed us with endless meme.s quotes, and fights, but that's a bout it. For a show that was initially created to help reform these "bad girls", it quickly became a guilty pleasure because of the nonstop conflicts in the house. Unlike shows like Survivor, Too Hot To Handle, or Love is Blind, there's no prize- be it money or a new partner. However, some for the former bad girls like Tanisha Thomas, Natalie Nunn, the Clermont Twins, Dreamdoll, and Winter, have all been able to angle their time on the show into reality TV or entertainment careers. Though the show went off the air over 5 years ago, some of the girls are still stirring up drama on their spinoffs, Baddies.

Bonding and bickering occur when seven self-proclaimed 'bad girls' share a house. Bad Girls Club (BGC) is an American reality television series created by Jonathan Murray for the Oxygen network in the United States. The show focuses on the altercations and physical confrontations of seven highly aggressive, quarrelsome, and unruly women. Each of the women tend to have psychological and behavioral problems. Mischievously sexual and rascally moments are also captured among the women. All seven women have different backgrounds and personalities. They are introduced to the show based off their capacity to be a "charismatic, tough chick." The cast, deemed "bad girls", enjoy a luxurious lifestyle in a fine mansion for three months, during which they must obey specified rules. Their lives inside and outside of the house are chronicled and recorded by the production team.

title: Bad Girls Club: Back 4 More - 16. "Reunion Part 3"
description:
The BGC4 Bad Girls reunite in sunny Los Angeles, California with scores to settle, and feuds to put to an end.

I just wanted to start off by saying thank you to everyone who watched this season or any other season that I have uploaded. I also wanted to thank you all for being patient with me. I know the reunion took a while to get up, but a bitch been busy lol and it's hard to keep up with scheduling cause sims can be soooo unpredictable. It's so crazy to me how I went from a tragic first season to now, and I want to continue to thank y'all for staying along for the ride lol. I'm being cheesy, but it's real shit, I wouldn't be here without the continuous support and the funny comments. Y'all be so funny in the comments, you have no idea! I really be cracking up. I'm reading the comments from the reunion trailer I uploaded earlier today and seeing y'all get so hype makes me excited for y'all to watch lol, thank y'all for that. And omg I just wanted to apologize for my text going fast sometimes lol. I be watching back like DAMN, BITCH, I AINT EVEN SEE WHAT SHE SAID! But you live and you learn, yannoe? Shout out to you if you made it to the end of this long mushy ass message lol. I hope you guys enjoyed this reunion, and once again, thank you for all the support. Love y'all.
Cheaa
Young Money

title: Interview with Shannon Sarich from Bad Girls Club
description:
*Shannon comes in on 27:15*

Facebook: Out The Box Radio Show
Instagram: @otb_radioshow
Hosts: Justin Martin (@Kendoll_JP) and Jonee Simmons (@Jojo_Latrice)

We sat down with friend to the show and returning guest Shannon Sarich #Shanrock from Season 10 of Bad Girls Club and WE TV's Bridezillas for an exclusive look into her life now as a Bad Girl turned Boss! We dive into her experience on both reality series, talk about upcoming shows, and her new restaurant and bar that will be opening in 2021! 

For all you BGC fans, Shannon confirmed the rumors of a BGC OG Reunion show was true and in fact they will be starting filming in October 2020 for the reunion series. This will air on OnlyFans, so make sure you subscribe if you want to see the baddest of the bad girls in action! So far it is confirmed to have 5-8 of  the bad girl OG's living in a house in Atlanta for 2-3 weeks.

Out the Box Radio has been here to entertain you for nearly 5 years. After a long journey we are finally coming to an end. Shannon surprised us as our final guest interview on the series. And our show finale will air on 10/22/20 and will host some familiar faces to the show for a last and final goodbye. Be sure to check out the live finale on www.rippedradionetwork.com and FB watch at Ripped Radio Network and Out The Box Radio Show. You can watch all our previous interviews and shows on Facebook and right here on YouTube. As always, we hope to entertain you again very soon!
